<paragraph id="8BE236F59D64FFD3FF02FDC030FEFC45" blockId="24.[167,775,558,916]" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D64FFD3FF02FDC0323CFD96" box="[168,775,558,583]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D64FFD3FF02FDC03071FD97" bold="true" box="[168,330,558,582]" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">Identification.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D769D64FFD3FEF3FDC13327FD97" box="[345,540,559,582]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Monstera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pittieri">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D64FFD3FEF3FDC13327FD97" box="[345,540,559,582]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">Monstera pittieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises nomadic
</emphasis>
vines with long internodes, small blades, sometimes perforated, entire margins; inconspicuous primary lateral veins, and short peduncles. On Cerro Pirre, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D769D64FFD3FD14FD7D31EDFD1D" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Monstera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pittieri">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D64FFD3FD14FD7D31EDFD1D" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">M. pittieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species of the genus that comprises adult plants with usually entire blades with inconspicuous primary lateral veins and short peduncles (up to 
<quantity id="4CA59B109D64FFD3FD25FD1933F8FCDF" box="[655,707,759,783]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" unit="cm" value="4.0">4 cm</quantity>
long). This species could be confused with juvenile individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D769D64FFD3FF45FCD4331DFC80" authority="(Schott) Engl." authorityName="Engl." baseAuthorityName="Schott" box="[239,550,825,849]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Monstera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="24" pageNumber="675" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spruceana">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D64FFD3FF45FCD430BDFC80" box="[239,390,826,849]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="675">M. spruceana</emphasis>
(Schott) Engl.
</taxonomicName>
, which differs by its appressed habit and juvenile plants with leaves tightly appressed to the substrate.
</paragraph>
